{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type: "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 03 — Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)\n",
    "\n",
    "Now that we have a clean dataset, let's dive in and see what the NYC Airbnb market looks like. We'll explore prices, locations, host behavior, and more.\n",
    "\n",
    "**What we're looking for:**\n",
    "- How are prices distributed?\n",
    "- Which boroughs are the most expensive?\n",
    "- What's the deal with host listings (single vs. multi-listers)?\n",
    "- Is there any seasonality in the reviews?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Setup & Data Load"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visual settings\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style='whitegrid', palette='muted')\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (10, 6)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Colors for our boroughs\n",
    "BOROUGH_COLORS = {\n",
    "    'Manhattan': '#E63946', \n",
    "    'Brooklyn': '#457B9D', \n",
    "    'Queens': '#2A9D8F', \n",
    "    'Bronx': '#F4A261', \n",
    "    'Staten Island': '#8338EC'\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load the cleaned data\n",
    "data_path = Path('../data/processed/airbnb_nyc_cleaned.csv')\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv(data_path)\n",
    "df['last_review'] = pd.to_datetime(df['last_review'])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Dataset loaded: {len(df)} rows\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Price Distribution\n",
    "Let's see how much people are charging. We'll look at the raw price and a log-transformed version since prices usually have a long tail."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(15, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.histplot(df['price'], bins=50, ax=ax1, color='skyblue')\n",
    "ax1.set_title('Price Distribution')\n",
    "ax1.axvline(df['price'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: ${df[\"price\"].median():.0f}')\n",
    "ax1.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.histplot(np.log1p(df['price']), bins=50, ax=ax2, color='salmon')\n",
    "ax2.set_title('Log-Price Distribution')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**What we see:** Most listings are around $100 per night, but there's a long tail of luxury listings. The log-distribution looks much more \"normal,\" which is helpful for statistics later."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Borough Breakdown\n",
    "Where are the listings, and where is it most expensive?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(15, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Listings by Borough\n",
    "sns.countplot(data=df, x='neighbourhood_group', palette=BOROUGH_COLORS, ax=ax1, \n",
    "              order=df['neighbourhood_group'].value_counts().index)\n",
    "ax1.set_title('Number of Listings by Borough')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Median Price by Borough\n",
    "sns.barplot(data=df, x='neighbourhood_group', y='price', estimator=np.median, \n",
    "            palette=BOROUGH_COLORS, ax=ax2, order=df['neighbourhood_group'].value_counts().index)\n",
    "ax2.set_title('Median Price by Borough')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**What we see:** Manhattan and Brooklyn dominate the market. Unsurprisingly, Manhattan has the highest prices, while Brooklyn is a close second in volume but more affordable."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Room Types\n",
    "How does the type of room affect the price and availability?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "sns.boxplot(data=df, x='room_type', y='price', palette='Set2')\n",
    "plt.ylim(0, 500) # clip for better visibility\n",
    "plt.title('Price Distribution by Room Type')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**What we see:** Entire homes/apartments are significantly more expensive than private or shared rooms. Shared rooms are the cheapest option, as expected."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Host Behavior: Single vs. Multi-Listers\n",
    "Are these hosts regular people or professional property managers?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df['host_type'] = df['host_listing_count'].apply(lambda x: 'Multi-Lister' if x > 1 else 'Single-Lister')\n",
    "host_counts = df['host_type'].value_counts(normalize=True) * 100\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))\n",
    "host_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['#457B9D', '#E63946'])\n",
    "plt.title('Percentage of Listings by Host Type')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Percentage (%)')\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=0)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"About {host_counts['Multi-Lister']:.1f}% of listings come from hosts with multiple properties.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Seasonality & Activity\n",
    "When do people leave reviews? This gives us a hint about when listings are most active."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df['review_month'] = df['last_review'].dt.month\n",
    "month_order = ['Jan', 'Feb', 'Mar', 'Apr', 'May', 'Jun', 'Jul', 'Aug', 'Sep', 'Oct', 'Nov', 'Dec']\n",
    "\n",
    "monthly_activity = df['review_month'].value_counts().sort_index()\n",
    "monthly_activity.index = [month_order[int(m)-1] for m in monthly_activity.index]\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "sns.barplot(x=monthly_activity.index, y=monthly_activity.values, color='teal')\n",
    "plt.title('Review Activity by Month (Last Review)')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Number of Reviews')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**What we see:** There's a massive spike in reviews in June and July. This confirms that summer is the peak season for NYC travel."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Correlation Heatmap\n",
    "Let's see how our variables relate to each other."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cols_to_corr = ['price', 'minimum_nights', 'review_count', 'review_rate_month', 'availability_365', 'host_listing_count']\n",
    "corr = df[cols_to_corr].corr()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))\n",
    "sns.heatmap(corr, annot=True, cmap='RdBu_r', center=0)\n",
    "plt.title('Correlation Heatmap')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Summary of Findings\n",
    "- **Price**: Heavily skewed, with Manhattan being the most expensive borough.\n",
    "- **Volume**: Manhattan and Brooklyn hold the vast majority of listings.\n",
    "- **Hosts**: About 1/3 of listings are managed by multi-listers (professionals).\n",
    "- **Timing**: Summer is definitely the busiest time for Airbnb in NYC.\n",
    "\n",
    "Next, we'll run some statistical tests to see if these differences are actually significant."
   ]
  }
 ],
